Author: PHILLIPPS
Vol / Page: 45
Edition:
Quote: SILVERSIDE <i>Argentina elongata</i> Hutton. According to Waite the silverside is yellowish or silvery with very pale brown semi-cross bands, at least in the young, and a polished silvery band along the middle of the sides. The eye is blue.
